    <h1 id="bookh1">Prenatal Care - 1st Month</h1>

    <h3>Nutrition</h3>
    <p>
        During the 1st month of pregnancy, it's essential to maintain a healthy diet to support the development of your baby. Focus on the following:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Consume a variety of fruits and vegetables for essential nutrients.</li>
        <li>Ensure an adequate intake of folic acid and prenatal vitamins.</li>
        <li>Include whole grains and lean proteins in your meals.</li>
        <li>Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Exercises</h3>
    <p>
        Regular exercise is crucial to staying healthy during pregnancy. Here are some safe exercises for the 1st month:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Walking or brisk walking is an excellent low-impact choice.</li>
        <li>Swimming can help reduce joint strain and improve circulation.</li>
        <li>Prenatal yoga or gentle stretching exercises can improve flexibility and relaxation.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Remember to consult your healthcare provider before starting any exercise routine or making significant dietary changes.
    </p>

